          "body": "## Summary\n\nTwo methods named in the `pd-ocr-labeler-spa` page-payload spec are not present in pd-book-tools today. Filing for tracking; the SPA works around both for now.\n\n## 1. `Page.merge_words(targets)`\n\nThe spec ([`pd-ocr-labeler-spa/specs/23-page-payload-backend.md` §9](https://github.com/ConcaveTrillion/pd-ocr-labeler-spa/blob/main/specs/23-page-payload-backend.md)) lists `page.merge_words(targets)` as the canonical call for `POST /words/merge`. Today pd-book-tools exposes only the per-line variants:\n\n- `pd_book_tools/ocr/block.py:737` — `Line.merge_adjacent_words(word_index, direction)`\n- `pd_book_tools/ocr/block.py:785` — `Line.merge_word_left(word_index)`\n- `pd_book_tools/ocr/block.py:789` — `Line.merge_word_right(word_index)`\n\nThe SPA route is `POST /words/{li}/{wi}/merge` with `{direction: 'left'|'right'}`, so the per-line API is the natural fit. A `Page.merge_words(targets)` wrapper would only matter if/when the SPA grows a collective merge endpoint.\n\n**Workaround in SPA spec-23-C2 (#316):** call `page.lines[line_index].merge_word_left(word_index)` / `merge_word_right(word_index)` directly.\n\n## 2. `Page.erase_pixels(bbox, fill_value=255)`\n\nThe spec lists `page.erase_pixels(bbox, fill_value=255)` for `POST /words/{li}/{wi}/erase-pixels`. pd-book-tools has no such method; the legacy `pd-ocr-labeler` implements it inline at `pd_ocr_labeler/state/page_state.py:1802` (`erase_pixels_rect`), which mutates `page.cv2_numpy_page_image[top:bottom, left:right] = fill_value` then calls `_finalize_bbox_edit(page)`.\n\n**Workaround in SPA spec-23-C2 (#316):** the SPA handler mutates `page.cv2_numpy_page_image` in place (same shape as legacy) and calls `page.finalize_page_structure()`. pd-book-tools should consider absorbing this routine so all Page consumers get it.\n\n## Acceptance\n\nTracking issue, not a feature request — close when either method lands in pd-book-tools, or when the SPA agent confirms the workaround is sufficient long-term.\n\n## Refs\n\n- pd-ocr-labeler-spa#316 — spec-23-C2 word geometry mutations.\n- pd-ocr-labeler-spa#315 — spec-23-C1 (related: pd-book-tools#52 for `Word.set_validated`).",
          "closedAt": "2026-05-19T04:56:51Z",
